# PURPOSE:
#   Verifies whether KWin's JS scripting sandbox exposes Qt's dynamic
#   property mechanism (setProperty / property) on window objects.
#
#   This is the foundation of the session-persistent window tracking UUID
#   approach: if it works, we can stamp a UUID onto each window at restore
#   time and retrieve it later for drift-correction without relying on
#   internalId (which changes between reboots).
#
# WHAT IS TESTED:
#   1. w.setProperty("kwinlib_uuid", someValue)  — write a custom property
#   2. w.property("kwinlib_uuid")                — read it back immediately
#   3. Load a second script and read the same property — confirming it
#      persists on the QObject between separate script loads
#
# USAGE:
#   python3 kwin_property_test.py --id "{uuid-of-any-open-window}"
#
#   Get a UUID from:  python3 kwin_probe.py -- thunderbird
